Life before 10th was like full of possibilities. No division, no feeling of superiority or inferiority among mates. We all were together and thought to be together till very end. 

What happened after 10th....?

Priorities kicked in. "Life ain't short buddy,", says my father, "you got to know what you want and even if you don't know what you want, you have to choose a track because time ain't stop for nobody. You got to move on."

Who can argue with that, I mean, that's reality. You don't know who you are, you don't know what you want and you don't know where you are going, thinking about stopping in the middle of the road full of crowd which is constantly moving forward, little do they know 'where' and more like they 'guess' where this road going lead them and you standing still and tall for a second, closing your eyes asking yourself a question, a question that will give you immeasurable suffering before providing you with the uttermost important and truthful answer of your existence, an answer that will solve all your resolves and will clear all your doubts, an answer that'll provide you with the sense of belongingness, an answer, which holds the power of synchronizing your past, present and future.
.
