I pre-ordered this book by @beckywadewriter, probably as soon as such a thing was possible. I waited for it eagerly. I admired it when it arrived. I read the prequel novella.

But I haven't read Stay With Me yet üò¨ Not because I haven't wanted to, but because I don't want to finish reading it. I don't want to not have it to look forward to anymore. It's almost like I've been saving it for a time when I REALLY need the pick-me-up.

This last year or so has been peppered with some doozies of awful experiences. Experiences that have sent me running to my faith, yes, but also to the escape of some very special books. What if I need that again?

Well, I guess I'll just have to reread this one, because I'm taking it off the shelf - life's too short to save it forever üòÜ

So. Anyone else do this? Put off a book you expect to adore simply so you still have it to look forward to? 

Please say it's not just me...

